     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">First, the CO supported China&apos;s emergency response and recovery by focusing on vulnerable populations. This included saving lives of COVID-19 patients who were critically ill and front-line responders, through the provision of medical equipment (584,374 USD of clinical electrocardiogram monitors, infusion pumps, 10,000 sets of protective clothing). 
Second, the CO provided technical leadership on the UN socio-economic impact assessment, which provides insights on effective policy prescriptions, particularly that with a focus on the pandemic&apos;s impact on the most vulnerable. Drawing from the assessment findings sampling 5044 individuals in 1,183 households, UNDP utilized the TRAC resources in 5 counties across 5 provinces in China for recovery support. 
Third, the CO implemented activities to help the most vulnerable population to build back better. Urgent livelihood needs of 400 vulnerable households (1,600 villagers) in Zhangwan (Hubei) were addressed due to UNDP&apos;s support on live streaming for e-commerce. Local farmers attracted 2.1 million customers through the livestreaming and increased their sales. Challenges in managing information and finance for local businesses were addressed as UNDP set up an information management platform, currently used by 8 businesses.
Fourth, the CO enhanced local public health and other basic social services, including education, in Neixiang (Henan), Zhouqu (Gansu) and Yilong (Sichuan), during the COVID and to prepare for future pandemics. 85000 students in Neixiang gained access to psychological support and received better education, as UNDP trained 960 teachers across the county on psychological support and communications. 680 patients (392 are female) in 19 villages directly benefited from the medical equipment donated by UNDP in Zhouqu; 40 doctors and nurses were fully trained to use the donated respiratory machine; 10 clinical electrocardiogram monitors and 50 first-aid kits. In Yilong, 10 villages received PPE and doctors and nurses in 5 hospitals were trained on epidemiology investigation and monitoring. Also, UNDP helped Yilong establish a long-term collaborative network with West China Hospital of Sichuan University to receive continuous technical support and guidance for pandemic control. 
Additionally, education recovery plans were developed in communities in Chengbu (Hunan) focusing on LNOB. 1,920 teachers have enhanced capacity on online education as UNDP mapped out the local education improvement needs and provided 8 training courses.
The 2020 TRAC (175,000 USD) managed to leverage and mobilize another 1,005,046.50 USD to directly benefit 4 additional counties in 4 other provinces, in addition the Zhangwan District of Shiyan City in Hubei, the epicenter of the COVID-19 in 2020, as proposed in the application document.</narrative>
      </comment>
